        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4353880615" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9509279813395116500">Author Anne Michaud is an award winning journalist and author whose work has raised public awareness, broadened reader engagement and resulted in systematic change. Anne has covered politicians for decades and has done a lot of research and has the knowledge, so in my opinion is the perfect person to have written this book.<br/><br/>I’m sure many of us have heard the stories covered by the media on many occasions of the infidelity and other scandals of many politicians, however Anne goes beyond the headli</span>
  <span id="freeText9509279813395116500" style="display:none">Author Anne Michaud is an award winning journalist and author whose work has raised public awareness, broadened reader engagement and resulted in systematic change. Anne has covered politicians for decades and has done a lot of research and has the knowledge, so in my opinion is the perfect person to have written this book.<br /><br />I’m sure many of us have heard the stories covered by the media on many occasions of the infidelity and other scandals of many politicians, however Anne goes beyond the headlines and delves into the stories of the wives who decided to stand by their men. Anne profiles these eight women in history and offers insight and a little understanding of the personal and public struggles of these women and reasons behind “Why They Stay”.<br /><br />I loved Why They Stay and found it as entertaining and engaging as it was well-written. I have to say it has most definitely changed my opinions on some things, and it made me realise how ignorance influences a persons decisions and opinions, and how there could always be a lot more happening beneath the surface that we’re otherwise unaware of. This is well worth a read even if you only have a passing interest in politics and what goes on behind the scenes.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9509279813395116500" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
