<div id="review_4492380396" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4492380396" />
    <a title="Evelyn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20756278-evelyn"><img alt="Evelyn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1566798606p2/20756278.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4492380396?book_show_action=true">Jan 21, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Evelyn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Evelyn" href="/user/show/20756278-evelyn">Evelyn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/20756278-evelyn?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4492380396" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14666369370399655794">I found this quite interesting, especially the four couples that I was familiar with. I still don&apos;t personally understand why women stick by men who are so unworthy of them. I guess I understand a bit more why. The author obviously did quite a bit of research and the book was well done. One little nitpick. Lately, I keep reading books that spell the word &quot;rein&quot; incorrectly. Especially in the phrase, &quot;free rein.&quot; Another book used the word reign at least three times for the &quot;reins&quot; of a horse. I </span>
  <span id="freeText14666369370399655794" style="display:none">I found this quite interesting, especially the four couples that I was familiar with. I still don't personally understand why women stick by men who are so unworthy of them. I guess I understand a bit more why. The author obviously did quite a bit of research and the book was well done. One little nitpick. Lately, I keep reading books that spell the word "rein" incorrectly. Especially in the phrase, "free rein." Another book used the word reign at least three times for the "reins" of a horse. I miss the days of hardly ever finding errors in books. Ms. Michaud used the wrong spelling only once, I think. Other than that, I don't remember any other glaring errors. I would recommend this book to people curious about how the other half lives, especially rich politicians. I have to admit that I feel sorrier for the children of these flawed marriages.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14666369370399655794" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


