<div id="review_4506692586" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4506692586" />
    <a title="Maria Rivas-mc" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22099410-maria-rivas-mc"><img alt="Maria Rivas-mc" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1600106087p2/22099410.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4506692586?book_show_action=true">Jan 26, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maria Rivas-mc" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maria Rivas-mc" href="/user/show/22099410-maria-rivas-mc">Maria Rivas-mc</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4506692586" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2761511900978323407">For much of the time reading “Why They Stay”, the mid 19th century proverbial saying - “Politics makes strange bedfellows “ - has been going around in my mind. <br/><br/>The meaning then (according to Oxford reference) was that political alliances in a common cause may bring together those of widely differing views. Unquestionably, while all the women profiled factored in the best interests of their children, for most of them, the goal of what was right for the country was also at the heart of their decis</span>
  <span id="freeText2761511900978323407" style="display:none">For much of the time reading “Why They Stay”, the mid 19th century proverbial saying - “Politics makes strange bedfellows “ - has been going around in my mind. <br /><br />The meaning then (according to Oxford reference) was that political alliances in a common cause may bring together those of widely differing views. Unquestionably, while all the women profiled factored in the best interests of their children, for most of them, the goal of what was right for the country was also at the heart of their decisions; self-interest trailed behind. This led them to a lifetime of tangible service in various spheres in spite of the immense personal disappointments and having to rise above ridicule and pity. <br /><br />Except, perhaps, for Melania Trump whose decisions, from the evidence presented, are carefully calculated based on benefits to her and her son. She certainly has not demonstrated the level of patriotism as seen in previous First Ladies, one that goes beyond lip service to a cause. Much would have to do with lessons learnt in an upbringing where belonging to Communist Party groups could bring a better standard of life and what is best for the family is the litmus test in decision-making.<br /><br />Anne Michaud notes that “this generation’s questions are not about adultery, but they are still about morality, from sexual assault to demands for sex to promote careers”. Melania Trump’s response was to recognize her moment of power and renegotiate her pre nuptial agreement. In that sense, I agree that she best fills the traits of a White Queen as posited by the author and is most like Elizabeth Woodville, a 15th century commoner in England’s War of the Roses and the original White Queen, who “ignored Edward IV’s promiscuity in favor of wielding power”.<br /><br />I thought the book well researched and works even when the White Queen theory seemed iffy to me. I enjoyed the dive into the lives of these women and sucked up the disappointment I sometimes felt in the once hidden lives of their spouses.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2761511900978323407" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

