<div id="review_4525589790" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4525589790" />
    <a title="Lynn Bates" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/118000455-lynn-bates"><img alt="Lynn Bates" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4525589790?book_show_action=true">Feb 03, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lynn Bates" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lynn Bates" href="/user/show/118000455-lynn-bates">Lynn Bates</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4525589790" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6789962076614333879">I very rarely read non fiction but liked the premise of this book. The author discusses famous political couples who have been involved in sex scandals and explores why the wives decide to stay or leave the marriage. There are some very famous couples such as the Clintons, Trumps and Kennedys and some I was unfamiliar with, as not au fait with American politics. However this didn’t detract. I found it fascinating that such accomplished women can make the decision that public humiliation isn’t en</span>
  <span id="freeText6789962076614333879" style="display:none">I very rarely read non fiction but liked the premise of this book. The author discusses famous political couples who have been involved in sex scandals and explores why the wives decide to stay or leave the marriage. There are some very famous couples such as the Clintons, Trumps and Kennedys and some I was unfamiliar with, as not au fait with American politics. However this didn’t detract. I found it fascinating that such accomplished women can make the decision that public humiliation isn’t enough for them to leave their partner. The emotional impact of infidelity must be immense, particularly when played out in the public arena. The book is well written and full of researched backstory to enable the reader to understand the context. There is a scoring system the author uses which I did lose track of a little but this wasn’t particularly important for me to enjoy the book. Overall an interesting and intriguing book I would recommend. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6789962076614333879" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


