<div id="review_4411808815" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4411808815" />
    <a title="Christina F" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/44705895-christina-f"><img alt="Christina F" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1641061728p2/44705895.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4411808815?book_show_action=true">Dec 27, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Christina F" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Christina F" href="/user/show/44705895-christina-f">Christina F</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4411808815" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3316019820339970645">Why They Stay: Sex, Scandals, Deals and Hidden Agendas of Nine Political Wives by Anne Michaud is a very intriguing book. We know about these couples from their politics but Anne takes us inside their personal lives. I often wonder why I hear about scandals among political couples and why the wives stick around when it is clear their husband is being unfaithful. Anne talked about different traits and how they may impact a couple staying together such as submitting to tradition, longing for secur</span>
  <span id="freeText3316019820339970645" style="display:none">Why They Stay: Sex, Scandals, Deals and Hidden Agendas of Nine Political Wives by Anne Michaud is a very intriguing book. We know about these couples from their politics but Anne takes us inside their personal lives. I often wonder why I hear about scandals among political couples and why the wives stick around when it is clear their husband is being unfaithful. Anne talked about different traits and how they may impact a couple staying together such as submitting to tradition, longing for security, responsibility for the family, and ambition to build and bequeath a legacy. As she goes through each couple you learn more about their personal lives, including things that happened in their childhood and help shape them into who they are today and as to why they stayed in unfaithful relationships. You also learn about how it affects the children. It was sad listening to the children of Eleanor and Franklin Roosevelt and all the marriages and divorces they went through. It seemed like stability, taking care of the family, security, and submitting to tradition were very common themes among all the couples. I found it especially interesting learning about Bill and Hillary Clinton as they are the couple I am most familiar with and saw a lot of it as it was happening. But again I didn’t know anything about their personal lives at the time. Oftentimes women are too harsh on themselves and have to deal with the stigma of divorce if they decide to go that route. It seemed like with some of the couples, such as Bill and Hillary, that it may have helped Hillary build her legacy as well. A very interesting read that was difficult to put down. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3316019820339970645" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


